    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix E1AP Bearer Context Modification Response Handler Task ID and Context Tracking\n\n### Summary\nThe `e1apCUCP_handle_BEARER_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_RESPONSE` function was using an incorrect task ID (`TASK_CUUP_E1`) instead of the proper CU-CP task ID (`TASK_CUCP_E1`). This caused messages to be allocated with wrong context and potentially led to improper message routing.\n\nAdditionally, the function was missing proper association ID tracking and error logging, making debugging difficult when message decoding failed.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Fixed task ID from `TASK_CUUP_E1` to `TASK_CUCP_E1` for message allocation\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Added missing error logging for decode failures  \n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Added proper association ID tracking via `msg->ittiMsgHeader.originInstance = assoc_id`\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Added instance parameter handling to match other E1AP handlers\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Applied same fixes to corresponding failure handler function\n\n"
}